<title>UK: South West Water up on bid speculation.</title>
<headline>South West Water up on bid speculation.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in South West Water rallied to a three-month high amid increasing bid talk, dealers said.</p>
<p>By 1049 GMT, the shares were trading at 660p, up 11.  </p>
<p>Dealers said a report in the Financial Times hightlighted the recent speculation, noting three possible U.S. predators, all electricity utilities. Executives from the U.S. utility concerns were said to have been in London this past week, the newspaper said.</p>
<p>&quot;The bid talk has been around for quite a few days now,&quot; said one market maker, noting the 10.4 percent increase in the value of the shares during the past week.</p>
<p>--Debra Sherman, London newsroom +44 171 542 4026</p>
